english help for example if someone asks you if you're not bored and you're not bored do you answer back no i'm not bored or yes i'm not bored in english being asked a negative question and a positive question are pretty much the same thing q are you bored a no i am not bored q are you not bored a no i am not bored this is because the not in the second question isn't serving to ask if someone is not bored it's asking are you not which is a longer way of asking aren't you q aren't you bored a no i am not bored this question format is generally used when the asker expects a yes answer it's akin to putting isn't it at the end of a sentence q this is boring isn't it a no this is not boring this is why a usage that appears to be a double negative something that is incorrect in english is actually correct i hope i made that clear enough Chess strategy and tactics Chess terminology Endgame Time Out of Mind Checkmate Dominoes Kasparov versus The World Shogi Chess problem terminology Baroque chess Chess problem Cribbage 2000 Australian Grand Prix Fischer Random Chess Helpmate Hey Jude Chess opening Poker jargon Theory of conduct Norway national football team She Loves You Sample chess game Wa shogi Taikyoku shogi French Defence Milton H. Erickson Fast bowling Judkins shogi Chu shogi 1957 World Series Satchel Paige Yari shogi Algebraic chess notation Cannon shogi Sydney Riot of 1879 Australian words Shaggy dog story Tai shogi Maka dai dai shogi Rules of chess Minishogi About a Boy Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film) Computer chess Dai shogi Debugging Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Xiangqi Blood on the Tracks Stuttering Witches (Discworld) Lucid dreaming Ty Cobb Microshogi Iron Maiden Tenjiku shogi Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Wonderland (McFly album) A Day in the Life Highway 61 Revisited Avenue Q CPU cache Pitaten Extreme Programming Equine conformation Heian dai shogi Chess variant Tonality Past teachings of Prem Rawat Eight queens puzzle The Gam